# uv
# uv.lock is COMMITTED — required for reproducible Docker builds (uv sync --frozen)


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Data boundary — public distribution must never include raw OHLCV.
#
# Strategy:
#   /data/              — ignored: raw, processed, and universe Parquet files.
#                         All raw OHLCV (open/high/low/close/volume) lives here.
#   results/            — COMMITTED: pre-computed JSON, HTML, and schema sidecars.
#                         Enforced by test_public_data_boundary_files.py.
#   results/.tmp/        — ignored: ephemeral job state and export intermediates.
#   .env / .env.*        — ignored: credentials must never enter the image.
#   !.env.example        — whitelisted: safe reference for contributors.
#
# Violations of these rules are caught in CI by the Phase 6.4 boundary audit.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Market data — never commit raw or processed OHLCV (TradingView copyright)
# Leading slash anchors to repo root — does not affect src/csm/data/
/data/

# results/ IS committed — do not ignore
# Temporary export artifacts only
results/.tmp/

# Environment — credentials must never be committed
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

.github/instructions/
.github/prompts/
.github/copilot-instructions.md

.claude/settings.local.json